</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
JAPAN'S two largest shipping companies, Nippon Yusen Kaisha and Mitsui OSK
Lines, blamed their latest profits declines on a fall in imports to their
economically depressed domestic market, writes William Dawkins in Tokyo.
Nippon Yusen's revenue fell by 10 per cent to Y268bn (Dollars 2.47bn), in
