<HEADLINE>
FT  09 NOV 93 / Water cut-offs fall by 42%
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
WATER COMPANIES are cutting off far fewer households than last year for
failing to pay bills, figures published yesterday by the water industry
show.
The number of customers disconnected by the big 10 water and sewerage
companies in the six months to September was 3,362, a 42 per cent fall on
the corresponding period of 1992, the water industry said.
Disconnections by Anglian Water leapt from 87 last year to 410, however. The
company said it had tried last year to reach compromises with people who had
difficulties in paying. 'Now we are left with a hard core who won't pay at
all.'
