relief from the international creditors, Paul Adams reports from Lagos. The
move is likely to be resented by many people, who are suffering form high
inflation and falling living standards. But government and private sector
leaders say that it is necessary to cut out smuggling of fuel, reduce losses
in the state oil company and attract investment in the downstream oil and
gas sectors.
