FT  08 NOV 93 / World News in Brief: European Monetary System
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The gap between the Dutch guilder at the top of the grid and the Danish
krone at the bottom narrowed sharply last week as the krone rose at the
expense of the D-Mark. The Belgian franc remained above the French franc
despite Belgium's high public debt, which is being exacerbated by high
short-term interest rates. Currencies, Page 29
The chart shows the member currencies of the exchange rate mechanism
measured against the weakest currency in the system. Most of the currencies
are permitted to fluctuate within 15 per cent of agreed central rates
against the other members of the mechanism. The exceptions are the D-Mark
and the guilder which move in a 2.25 per cent band.
