FT  08 NOV 93 / UK Company News: Warburg director to retire
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By STEPHEN THOMPSON
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
MR PETER Wilmot-Sitwell is to retire as vice-chairman of SG Warburg and
chairman of Warburg Securities following the merchant bank's next annual
meeting, scheduled for June next year. He will, however, remain a
non-executive director at Warburg Securities. Mr Wilmot-Sitwell will be
succeeded by Mr Nick Verey.
Mr Wilmot-Sitwell is widely viewed as one of the architects of the few post
big-bang successes among UK merchant banks and broking firms. As senior
partner at Rowe &amp; Pitman, the stockbroker, he was instrumental in forging
the alliance between R&amp;P with Warburg, the merchant bank, Akroyd &amp; Smithers,
the stockjobber and Mullens, the gilt-edged specialist.
